Using this wonderful "banner-color indicator" method, we've just IMPROVED upon the Eisenhower method! OH SHIT, THAT'S THE POWER OF NOTION BABY! Create your color system and marvel at the wonders of sub-task-categorization 👍

NOTE: The gallery view displays your task's cover image as its preview. I recommend using Notion's provided colors to different tasks with various "importance" levels, or use the colors to indicate the amount of time / energy it'll take to complete.

For instance, all of these notes I'm typing here use a cool blue-red gradient, but you can use solid RED for hard tasks, or solid YELLOW for tasks that require attention, or solid BLUE for tasks that you need outside resources to complete. Whatever! Make up your own system and go wild!
